## Licensing

This repository uses a dual-license approach to reflect the different kinds of material it contains.

### Code
All source code files (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) are licensed under the **MIT License**.

See: `LICENSE-MIT`

### Content and Framework Material
All written content, explanatory text, diagrams, visual language descriptions, and materials describing the Consilient Design (CD) framework are licensed under the **Creative Commons Attribution–NonCommercial–ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)** license.

See: `LICENSE-CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0`

### Rationale
This separation allows the technical implementation to be freely reused and adapted, while ensuring the Consilient Design framework and its explanatory materials remain attributable, non-commercial, and shared under the same ethical conditions.

